  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I went to the school, and it was always understood, and again probably part of the German background, that I would someday be trained and-- professionally trained to take over the very successful firm of my father.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We had a firm with 50 coat-makers and two designers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my father often missed in his own professional training that he hadn't gotten the technical background that he felt was missing in his own background.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And therefore it was always understood that someday I would learn-- before I would take over, I would learn tailoring and designing and be sent to England to some weaving school or to some school-- the people who made the cloth for our fine custom suits, and be trained there so that I would have a complete, well-rounded background.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when I was 12 years old, I think it was the year before my bar mitzvah, my father came to the fantastic-- came up with a fantastic idea that-- told me that he would let me work in his workshop, and one of his tailors would teach me the basics of tailoring if I would bring up my Latin grades.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I went a couple of times.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It sounded very exciting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But after three or four or five times, I came to the conclusion that it was much easier to let my Latin grades go down if it meant that I wouldn't have to go into this ridiculous tailor training, which was partly part of my youthful arrogance and partly of my snobbism that was connected with this.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Because I never could quite understand why I had to be-- become a worker and be trained as a tailor before taking over the management of my father's firm.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But he insisted on it and that was understood.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
